{{Orphan|date=September 2011}}
{{Infobox book | image =CryoftheKalahari.jpg | image_size =200px | author= Mark & Delia Owens | name = ''Cry of the Kalahari'' | language = English | genre = Autobiography, Zoology, Wildlife | publisher= Robert Hartnoll Limited | release_date = 1984 | media_type = Hardcover, Paperback }} '''''Cry of the Kalahari''''' (1984) is an autobiographical book detailing two young American zoologists, Mark and Delia Owens, and their experience studying wildlife in the [[Kalahari desert]] in [[Botswana]] in the mid-1970s.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.people.com/people/archive/article/0,,20090354,00.html |title=Picks and Pans Review: Cry of the Kalahari |work=[[People (magazine)|People]] |author=Ralph Novak |date=April 8, 1985 |accessdate=July 2, 2014}}</ref> There they lived and worked for seven years in an unexplored area named Deception Valley in the [[Central Kalahari Game Reserve]].<ref>{{cite book |url= |title=Cry of the Kalahari |publisher=Houghton Mifflin Company |author=Mark & Delia Owens |year=1984 |isbn=0395322146}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://connection.ebscohost.com/c/book-reviews/7419336/cry-kalahari-book |title=Cry of the Kalahari (Book) |work=[[Library Journal]] |author=Laurie Tynan |date=November 1, 1984 |accessdate=July 3, 2014}} Abstract: Reviews the book 'Cry of Kalahari,' by Mark Owens and Delia Owens.</ref> With no roads and no people and the nearest civilization eight hours away they had only each other and the animals they studied as company, most of which had never seen humans before. Their research focused mainly on [[lions]], [[brown hyena]]s, [[jackals]] and other African carnivores. ''Cry of the Kalahari'' is the personal story of the Owens' encounters with these and a myriad of other animals and depicts their own struggle to live and work in such an inhospitable and unforgiving environment.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.owens-foundation.org/docs/kalahari2.htm |title=The Kalahari Years |publisher=Owens Foundation for Wildlife Conservation |author= |date= |accessdate=July 3, 2014}}</ref>
''Cry of the Kalahari'' was a national and international bestseller,<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.nytimes.com/1985/03/17/books/no-headline-102313.html |title=Best sellers |work=[[New York Times Best Seller List]] |author= |date=March 17, 1985 |accessdate=July 3, 2014}}</ref> translated into seven languages and is the 1985 [[John Burroughs Medal]] winner.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://research.amnh.org/burroughs/medal_award_list.html |title=John Burroughs Medal Award List |publisher=[[John Burroughs Medal]] |author= |date= |accessdate=July 3, 2014}}</ref>
