uous forest]] surrounded by a {{convert|56|m|ft|adj=mid|-wide}} earth bank that takes up a large part of the park.<ref name="dalby">{{cite web|title=Dalby Söderskog National Park |url=http://www.naturvardsverket.se/en/In-English/Start/Enjoying-nature/National-parks-and-other-places-worth-visiting/National-Parks-in-Sweden/Dalby-Soderskog-National-Park/ |publisher=Naturvårdsverket (Swedish Environmental Protection Agency) |accessdate=2009-02-26 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110326165208/https://www.naturvardsverket.se/en/In-English/Start/Enjoying-nature/National-parks-and-other-places-worth-visiting/National-Parks-in-Sweden/Dalby-Soderskog-National-Park/ |archivedate=2011-03-26 |df= }}</ref> |- !scope=row|[[Djurö National Park]] | [[Västra Götaland County]] | {{sort|{{commas|2400}}|{{convert|2400|ha|acre|0|abbr=on}}}} | 1991 |Djurö National Park consists of an [[archipelago]] with about 30 islands in Sweden's biggest lake, [[Vänern]].<ref name="Djurö">{{cite web| title=Djurö National Park| url=http://www.naturvardsverket.se/en/In-English/Start/Enjoying-nature/National-parks-and-other-places-worth-visiting/National-Parks-in-Sweden/Djuro-National-Park/| publisher=Naturvårdsverket (Swedish Environmental Protection Agency)| accessdate=2009-02-26| deadurl=yes| archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110326165214/http://www.naturvardsverket.se/en/In-English/Start/Enjoying-nature/National-parks-and-other-places-worth-visiting/National-Parks-in-Sweden/Djuro-National-Park/| archivedate=2011-03-26| df=}}</ref> |- !scope=row|{{sort|Farnebofjärden National Park|[[Färnebofjärden National Park]]}} | [[Dalarna County|Dalarna]], [[Gävleborg County|Gävleborg]], [[Uppsala County|Uppsala]], and [[Västmanland County|Västmanland]] counties | {{sort|{{commas|10100}}|{{convert|10100|ha|acre|0|abbr=on}}}} | 1998 | [[Dalälven|Dalälven River]] passes through the park and the uneven shoreline encloses over 200 islands and islets.<ref name="Färnebofjärden">{{cite web|ti