tional Park|[[Söderåsen National Park]]}} | [[Skåne County]] | {{sort|{{commas|1625}}|{{convert|1625|ha|acre|0|abbr=on}}}} | 2001 |The park features an especially contoured landscape with up to {{convert|90|m|ft|adj=mid|-deep}} ravines. The valleys are covered with broadleaf forest, mostly beech.<ref name="söderåsen">{{cite web| title=Söderåsen National Park| url=http://www.naturvardsverket.se/en/In-English/Start/Enjoying-nature/National-parks-and-other-places-worth-visiting/National-Parks-in-Sweden/Soderasen-National-Park/| publisher=Naturvårdsverket (Swedish Environmental Protection Agency)| accessdate=2009-02-26| deadurl=yes| archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110325115734/http://www.naturvardsverket.se/en/In-English/Start/Enjoying-nature/National-parks-and-other-places-worth-visiting/National-Parks-in-Sweden/Soderasen-National-Park/| archivedate=2011-03-25| df=}}</ref> |- !scope=row|[[Stenshuvud National Park]] | [[Skåne County]] | {{sort|{{commas|390}}|{{convert|390|ha|acre|0|abbr=on}}}} | 1986 |Stenshuvud is a hill that faces the Baltic Sea. Because the surrounding landscape is relatively flat, it can be seen from a great distance and has been used by [[seafarers]] as an aid to navigation at sea. Most of the area is covered with broadleaf forest.<ref name="stenshuvud">{{cite web| title=Stenshuvud National Park| url=http://www.naturvardsverket.se/en/In-English/Start/Enjoying-nature/National-parks-and-other-places-worth-visiting/National-Parks-in-Sweden/Stenshuvud-National-Park/| publisher=Naturvårdsverket Swedish Environmental Protection Agency| accessdate=2009-02-26}}</ref> |- !scope=row style="background:#CFECEC;"|[[Stora Sjöfallet National Park]]* | [[Norrbotten County]] | {{sort|{{commas|127800}}|{{convert|127800|ha|acre|0|abbr=on}}}} | 1909 |The park's northern portions lie in the [[Scandinavian Mountains]], home to some of Sweden's highest peaks. The lower hills in the park's southern part are covered with forest.<ref name="StoraSjöfallet">{{cite we