l-parks-and-other-places-worth-visiting/National-Parks-in-Sweden/Tiveden-National-Park/| publisher=Naturvårdsverket (Swedish Environmental Protection Agency)| accessdate=2009-02-26}}</ref> |- !scope=row|{{sort|Tofsingdalen National Park|[[Töfsingdalen National Park]]}} | [[Dalarna County]] | {{sort|{{commas|1615}}|{{convert|1615|ha|acre|0|abbr=on}}}} | 1930 |Töfsingdalen National Park consists of two mountain ridges separated by a valley covered with fields and virgin forest.<ref name="Töfsingdalen">{{cite web| title=Töfsingdalen National Park| url=http://www.naturvardsverket.se/en/In-English/Start/Enjoying-nature/National-parks-and-other-places-worth-visiting/National-Parks-in-Sweden/Tofsingdalen-National-Park/| publisher=Naturvårdsverket (Swedish Environmental Protection Agency)| accessdate=2009-02-26| deadurl=yes| archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110326165245/http://www.naturvardsverket.se/en/In-English/Start/Enjoying-nature/National-parks-and-other-places-worth-visiting/National-Parks-in-Sweden/Tofsingdalen-National-Park/| archivedate=2011-03-26| df=}}</ref> |- !scope=row|[[Tresticklan National Park]] | [[Västra Götaland County]] | {{sort|{{commas|2897}}|{{convert|2897|ha|acre|0|abbr=on}}}} | 1996 |This park contains a [[rift]] valley landscape and is one of the few remaining areas of pristine forest in southern Scandinavia.<ref name="Tresticklan">{{cite web| title=Tresticklan National Park| url=http://www.naturvardsverket.se/en/In-English/Start/Enjoying-nature/National-parks-and-other-places-worth-visiting/National-Parks-in-Sweden/Tresticklan-National-Park/| publisher=Naturvårdsverket (Swedish Environmental Protection Agency)| accessdate=2009-02-26}}</ref> |- !scope=row|[[Tyresta National Park]] | [[Stockholm County]] | {{sort|{{commas|2000}}|{{convert|2000|ha|acre|0|abbr=on}}}} | 1993 |Tyresta is a [[canyon|gorge]] landscape with stony slopes. The park, covered with pine forest, is one of the largest virgin forests in Sweden.<ref name="Tyresta">{{cite 